<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Timers Memory Leak</h1>
        <div class="description">
            <p><strong>Explanation:</strong> A timers leak occurs when timers (setInterval, setTimeout) are not properly cleared. These timers keep references to their callback functions and any variables used within those functions, preventing garbage collection.</p>
            <p><strong>Visualization:</strong> The blue blocks represent memory being allocated by the timer. Each interval adds more blocks, simulating increasing memory usage due to the timer not being cleared.</p>
            <p><strong>Example Code:</strong></p>
            <pre>
function startTimer() {
    setInterval(() => {
        console.log('Timer leak');
        // Simulate memory usage
        const leakArray = new Array(1000).fill('leak');
    }, 1000); // Timer that is never cleared
}
            </pre>
        </div>
        <button id="start-button">Start Leak</button>
        <div id="output"></div>
        <div class="visual" id="visual"></div>
    </div>
